"n.糕点，点心 【英】 n. 糕点，点心(sweet baked goods) 【记】 paste(浆糊)＋ry→面 糊做成的糕点 n. 烘烤过的糕点 【记】past = paste(n 浆糊, 面糊), try－努力用面糊做成糕点 【记】源自paste， 面糊做的东西；paste面糊 + tray 盘子，面糊放盘子里烤的糕点 【相关】pantry 餐具室, 食品室 pastry (n.)  mid-15c., ""food made with paste,"" not originally limited to sweets, from Middle English paste (see paste (n.)) + -ry. Probably influenced by Old French pastaierie ""pastry"" (Modern French pâtisserie), from pastoier ""pastry cook,"" from paste (see paste (n.)); also borrowed from Medieval Latin pasteria ""pastry,"" from Latin pasta. Specific sense of ""small confection made of pastry"" is from 1906. Pastry-cook attested from 1712."
